<text top="48" left="41" width="503" height="54" font="1">Managing social media </text>
<text top="154" left="58" width="912" height="34" font="5">Managing social media accounts: the reality of social media use in a </text>
<text top="190" left="58" width="974" height="34" font="5">company is that you as the “computer guy” might get landed with running </text>
<text top="226" left="58" width="396" height="34" font="5">the companies twitter account</text>
<text top="262" left="58" width="541" height="34" font="5">• Loosing out on social media accounts</text>
<text top="298" left="58" width="915" height="34" font="5">• Understanding the Streisand Effect and the permanence of social </text>
<text top="334" left="98" width="404" height="34" font="5">media activity effects all of this</text>
<text top="370" left="58" width="888" height="34" font="5">• Astroturfing reviews, where you use fake accounts to give good </text>
<text top="406" left="98" width="310" height="34" font="5">reviews of your product</text>
<text top="442" left="58" width="665" height="34" font="5">• Managing the level of interaction with your staff</text>
<text top="514" left="335" width="417" height="34" font="6"><i>Well, what harm can that do…?</i></text>
</page>
<page number="12" position="absolute" top="0" left="0" height="810" width="1080">
